  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The IBL environment is treated as a light source and using ray tracing a model is composited matrix (LTM). 6 Wang et al.",
    "(2009) classifies the approaches into three categories: (i) brute force (O' Toole et al. 2012; Hawkins et al. 2005), directly modeling the LTM, (ii) sparsity based (Garg et al. 2006; Masselus et al. 2003; Reddy et al. 2012), modeling a set of basis functions under the assumption that each row of the LTM can be linearly approximated, and (iii) coherence based (O'Toole and Kutulakos 2010; Wang et al. 2009; Fuchs et al. 2007), analysing the coherence reflectance field to acquire the LTM.",
    "The limitation with these methods is that they require multiple images under varying lighting condition, meaning for video this problem is more challenging to address.",
    "Interestingly, focus on cases (1) and (2) has shifted towards using LED panels to project virtual backgrounds as a practical solution.",
    "For case (1) foreground-background separation is made easy by replacing chroma screens with virtual backgrounds displayed live on interconnected LED panels."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
